# Rycode — Netlify response headers
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Netlify reads this file at deploy time and attaches the listed
# headers to every response that matches the path pattern.
#
# /* applies to every URL on the site.
#
# WHY THESE HEADERS?
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Content-Security-Policy (CSP) tells the browser exactly which
# script/style/image sources it's allowed to load. If an attacker
# ever managed to inject a <script src="evil.com"> tag into the
# page, the browser would refuse to run it because evil.com isn't
# on the allow-list. CSP is a containment policy — it doesn't stop
# bugs, it just shrinks the blast radius when they happen.
#
# X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
#   Stops browsers from "guessing" a file is HTML/JS when the
#   server said it was something else. Closes off a class of
#   MIME-confusion attacks.
#
# X-Frame-Options: DENY
#   Forbids any other site from loading rycode.dev in an <iframe>.
#   Defeats clickjacking — where an attacker overlays your real
#   page under their fake one and tricks users into clicking it.
#
# Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
#   When a visitor clicks a link off rycode.dev, only the origin
#   (https://rycode.dev) is sent in the Referer header — not the
#   full URL. Limits information leakage to third parties.
#
# Permissions-Policy
#   Explicitly tells the browser this site never needs camera,
#   mic, or geolocation. Even if a future bug somehow tries to
#   call those APIs, the browser will refuse.
#
# CSP NOTES — what's allowed and why
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
#   default-src 'self'           — by default, only load from rycode.dev
#   script-src                   — scripts from rycode.dev + Chart.js on
#                                  jsdelivr + the one inline bootstrap
#                                  script (allowed by its sha256 hash)
#   style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'
#                                — needed because we set inline style
#                                  attributes from JS (e.g. CSS custom
#                                  properties for tilt cards / charts)
#   img-src 'self' data:         — own images + base64 data: URIs
#   frame-ancestors 'none'       — same as X-Frame-Options: DENY but
#                                  newer / more granular
#   object-src 'none'            — blocks <object>/<embed>/<applet>
#   upgrade-insecure-requests    — auto-upgrades any stray http:// link
#                                  to https:// before the request goes out
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' https://cdn.jsdelivr.net 'sha256-e2g5HkZP+fghbsY1m7moq4GopOo7zRRaAHNyQ2Q7oSI='; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; object-src 'none'; upgrade-insecure-requests
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()
